Could this be related to how DateTime::createFromFormat interprets the date string (that does not have timezone in it) as UTC or local without DST and then on formating it it applies the DST.  In this case this is an issue for php.

Now we got the whole picture. because 2 AM becomes 3 AM, the interval from 2 to 3 AM does not exist and the DateTime::createFromFormat knows about it and it formats the date accordingly.

The only issue here is that the input data is invalid because that time does not exist in that timezone.
